data_path <- "C:/Users/digor/OneDrive/Documents/Projet_SCI1402_analyse_GTD/data/processed/gtd_clean.csv"

# Lecture des donnes
gtd_data <- read_csv(data_path, show_col_types = FALSE)

#                    2. DISTRIBUTIONS ET TENDANCES GNRALES

cat("\n\n=== CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS DE DISTRIBUTION ===\n")

## 
## === CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS DE DISTRIBUTION ===
# Distribution par type d'attaque
p1 <- ggplot(gtd_data, aes(x = attack_type)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "skyblue") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Distribution des Types d'Attaques",
       x = "Type d'attaque",
       y = "Nombre d'incidents")

print(p1)

# volution temporelle par type d'attaque
p2 <- gtd_data %>%
  count(year, attack_type) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = n, color = attack_type)) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "volution des Types d'Attaques dans le Temps",
       x = "Anne",
       y = "Nombre d'incidents",
       color = "Type d'attaque")

print(p2)

## 
## === CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS GOGRAPHIQUES ===
# Distribution par rgion
p3 <- ggplot(gtd_data, aes(x = region)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "skyblue") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Nombre d'Incidents par Rgion",

print(p3)

# Carte des incidents
world <- map_data("world")
p4 <- ggplot() +
  geom_map(data = world, map = world,
           aes(long, lat, map_id = region),
           color = "white", fill = "lightgray") +
  geom_point(data = gtd_data,
             aes(x = longitude, y = latitude, color = killed),
             alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_color_viridis() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Distribution Gographique des Incidents",
       color = "Nombre de victimes")

#                    4. ANALYSE DES VICTIMES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
cat("\n=== CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS DES VICTIMES ===\n")
## 
## === CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS DES VICTIMES ===
# Distribution des victimes
p5 <- ggplot(gtd_data, aes(x = killed)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 50, fill = "darkred", alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Distribution du Nombre de Victimes (chelle log)",
       x = "Nombre de victimes",
       y = "Frquence")

print(p5)
## Warning in scale_x_log10(): log-10 transformation introduced infinite values.
## Warning: Removed 98403 rows containing non-finite outside the scale range
## (`stat_bin()`).

# Victimes par rgion
p6 <- gtd_data %>%
  group_by(region) %>%
  summarize(total_killed = sum(killed, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(region, total_killed), y = total_killed)) +
  geom_col(fill = "darkred", alpha = 0.7) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Nombre Total de Victimes par Rgion",
       x = "Rgion",
       y = "Nombre total de victimes")

print(p6)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#                    5. ANALYSE DE CORRLATION
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
cat("\n=== CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS DE CORRLATION ===\n")
## 
## === CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS DE CORRLATION ===
# Matrice de corrlation
numeric_data <- gtd_data %>%
  select(killed, wounded, year) %>%
  cor(use = "complete.obs")

corrplot(numeric_data,
         method = "color",
         type = "upper",
         addCoef.col = "black",
         tl.col = "black",
         tl.srt = 45,
         title = "Matrice de Corrlation")

# Relation entre tus et blesss
p7 <- ggplot(gtd_data, aes(x = killed, y = wounded)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5, color = "darkred") +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "blue") +
  scale_x_log10() +
  scale_y_log10() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Relation entre Nombre de Tus et de Blesss",
       x = "Nombre de tus (log)",
       y = "Nombre de blesss (log)")

print(p7)
## Warning in scale_x_log10(): log-10 transformation introduced infinite values.

cat("\n=== CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS TEMPORELLES ===\n")
## 
## === CRATION DES VISUALISATIONS TEMPORELLES ===
# Tendance annuelle gnrale
p8 <- gtd_data %>%
  count(year) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = n)) +
  geom_line(color = "darkred") +
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", color = "blue") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "volution du Nombre d'Incidents par Anne",
       x = "Anne",
       y = "Nombre d'incidents")

print(p8)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

# Prtraitement des donnes : Regroupement par anne
gtd_data_summary <- gtd_data %>%
  group_by(iyear) %>%
  summarise(number_of_attacks = n())  # Compter le nombre d'attaques par anne

# Cration du graphique
ggplot(data = gtd_data_summary, aes(x = factor(iyear), y = number_of_attacks)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "steelblue") +  # Graphique en barres
  theme_minimal() +  # Utilisation d'un thme pur
  labs(title = "Number of terrorist attacks by year, worldwide",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Number of attacks") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)  # Format des chiffres avec sparateur de milliers

# Ajouter une colonne pour les couleurs 
gtd_data_summary <- gtd_data_summary %>%
  mutate(color = as.factor(iyear))

# Cration le graphique avec couleur dgrade
ggplot(data = gtd_data_summary, aes(x = factor(iyear), y = number_of_attacks, fill = iyear)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_fill_viridis(option = "plasma", direction = -1) +  # Palette dgrade
  labs(title = "Number of terrorist attacks by year, worldwide",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Number of attacks",
       fill = "Year") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)  # Format des nombres
